        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 11:48AM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 1147 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Dexter, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ann Arbor, Brighton, Milford, Dexter, Pinckney, Hamburg, South Lyon,
Whitmore Lake, Barton Hills, Hudson Mills Metropark, Island Lake
State Recreation Area, Delhi Mills, New Hudson, Pinckney State
Recreation Area, Hudson Mills, Lakeland, and Chilson.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
